hopobject.body: We'll need to take up references medicarepills.com A broad-based U.S. stock fund such as the Vanguard Total Market Index ETF represents most U.S. stocks. It's a worthy core vehicle that holds large-, medium- and small-capitalization companies. If you need growth in your portfolio and have retreated from stocks, it's still a good time to consider this index fund. The annual expenses are 0.05 percent annually, so it's a bargain. The fund has gained 21 percent for the year through September 20.
